 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Agent Lifecycle as Harvest/Seed — Topology-Aware Agent Management (SEED.md S5, ADR-TOPOLOGY-005, ADR-TOPOLOGY-006, INV-TOPOLOGY-003). BACKGROUND: An agent IS a bounded trajectory through attention space. The harvest/seed lifecycle manages agent lifecycle: SPAWN = braid seed (prime context), EXECUTE = work while k_eff decreases, HARVEST = extract knowledge, TERMINATE = context cleared, RESPAWN = fresh k_eff with updated seed. Braid is the coordination BRAIN (pure computation, no IO); the orchestrator (human/ntm/Claude Code) spawns and manages actual processes. Agent state tracked as :agent/* datoms. The topology plan outputs per-agent task lists, seed commands, and CARGO_TARGET_DIR assignments. R(t) routing becomes partition-aware: braid next --agent filters to assigned partition. This EPIC covers the braid topology plan CLI command and partition-aware R(t) routing."
